US Dept of Justice Crime Stats
http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/glance/viort.htm
Show violent crime in steep decline from 1994.  Now at lowest level ever.
Property crime has declined steadily from mid-70's to a third of that level.
Drug arrests have tripled from 1980
Number of people under 'correctional supervision' has more than tripled since 1980, with those serving prison terms is over 4x the 1980 rate.  Population of US increased 25% during this period (to 290M)

U.S Census Bureau
Poverty Rate at lowest levels in 70's, rose steeply from 1980.



